1 AN ACT relating to interment in state veterans' cemeteries and declaring an
2 emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. KRS 40.315 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) The Department of Veterans' Affairs shall establish and maintain state veterans'
6 cemeteries in the Commonwealth for the purpose of providing for the interment of
7 veterans of the[ United States] Armed Forces of the United States and for their
8 eligible next of kin, as determined by the department.
9 (2) Eligibility for interment at a Kentucky state veterans' cemetery shall include:
10 (a) Persons who are eligible for interment in a veterans' national cemetery
11 pursuant to 38 U.S.C. sec. 2402 and regulations promulgated thereunder;
12 and
13 (b) Any member of a reserve component of the Armed Forces, the Army
14 National Guard, or the Air National Guard not otherwise qualified in
15 paragraph (a) of this subsection, if:
16 1. The member completed the initial period of service as required by 10
17 U.S.C. sec. 651(a) and was discharged under conditions other than
18 dishonorable; or
19 2. The member of the Army National Guard or the Air National Guard
20 died while on state active duty or while serving under Title 32 of the
21 United States Code.
22 (3) For a person eligible under subsection (2)(b) of this section, the eligibility for
23 interment of the person's spouse, surviving spouse, minor child, and dependent
24 incapacitated child shall be determined pursuant to 38 U.S.C. sec. 2402(a)(5).
25 (4) The Kentucky state veterans' cemeteries shall be under the administrative authority
26 and control of the Department of Veterans' Affairs. The department[ of Veterans'
27 Affairs] may promulgate administrative regulations necessary to operate the
