2 (5)[(3)] The department shall provide interment service in accordance with 38
3 U.S.C. secs. 2404 and 2408.
4 (6) No person convicted of a state or federal criminal capital offense shall be eligible
5 for interment in a Kentucky state veterans' cemetery.
6 (7) The department[ of Veterans' Affairs] is authorized to seek federal and private
7 funding for the construction, renovation, and operation of Kentucky state veterans'
8 cemeteries.
9 Section 2. Whereas service members and their families deserve the dignity and
10 honor of being laid to final rest in a place sacred to the honor and memory of their service
11 and sacrifice, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage
12 and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
